abstract: Though the environmentalist Tom Steyer has vowed to sell his investments in companies that generate fossil fuels, the projects his hedge fund bankrolled may emit carbon for decades to come.
snippet: Though the environmentalist Tom Steyer has vowed to sell his investments in companies that generate fossil fuels, the projects his hedge fund bankrolled may emit carbon for decades to come.
lead_paragraph: To environmentalists across Australia, it is a baffling anachronism in an era of climate change: the construction of a 4,000-acre mine in New South Wales that will churn out carbon-laden coal for the next 30 years.

abstract: Supporters of the Old Bethpage Village Restoration hope the marketing power of World War II will reinvigorate the deteriorating county park.
snippet: Supporters of the Old Bethpage Village Restoration hope the marketing power of World War II will reinvigorate the deteriorating county park.
lead_paragraph: OLD BETHPAGE, N.Y. â€” The convoy rolled out with Jim Lennon at the wheel of a scout car, the kind of olive-drab machine with a gun above the windshield that Allied soldiers drove in World War II. As he gunned the engine and headed up a dirt road through a pasture, the split-levels of the Long Island suburbs seemed far away.

abstract: Somewhere between the re-emergent frozen yogurt and artisanal ice creams, there is soft serve, a staple that is due our love.
snippet: Somewhere between the re-emergent frozen yogurt and artisanal ice creams, there is soft serve, a staple that is due our love.
lead_paragraph: A few days a week at my office, we conduct something known as the 4 p.m. shame spiral. A small group of us makes a discreet exit from our building to the fro-yo joint across the street, where we pile all manner of cereal and macerated fruit over an overly generous portion of frozen yogurt that has oozed from a giant machine.

abstract: Getting a divorce late in life can sabotage retirement plans as assets are cut in half and expenses as a divorced single rise.
snippet: Getting a divorce late in life can sabotage retirement plans as assets are cut in half and expenses as a divorced single rise.
lead_paragraph: AFTER enduring a divorce four years ago, Mike Millerâ€™s vision for a golden retirement got an unexpected makeover. Mr. Miller had been married for more than 30 years, and now he was single. His longtime dream of a shared retirement was shattered. He was also facing another unwelcome outcome: living in a smaller home and taking fewer vacations.
